## 4. Core Beliefs & Design Principles

These principles guide every product, design, and engineering decision:

| Principle | Definition |
|-----------|------------|
| **Education-first** | Every recommendation is a learning opportunity. Every action should teach the user something. |
| **Transparency** | AI always explains the reasoning behind suggestions. Never be a black box. |
| **User control** | The app never executes trades automatically. The user approves every action. |
| **Accessibility** | Financial concepts are translated into simple, intuitive language. First-time investors should feel confident. |
| **Safety** | Beginner-friendly guardrails protect users from high-risk complexity. |
| **Personalization** | AI adapts to the user's goals, knowledge level, and risk tolerance. |

### Upgraded Core Principle for AI Role

> *"The AI provides probabilistic insights and educational explanations — not financial advice."*

The AI's role is positioned as **"educational guidance + decision support,"** NOT an autonomous financial advisor. All guarantee-style language (e.g., "you should buy") is eliminated.

