## 5. Product Experience Overview

From the moment a user joins, Finance Buddy feels like a **companion — not a tool**.

A user names their Finance Buddy, completes a short personalized onboarding quiz, and immediately receives a financial profile written in plain language. From there, their companion is always present: explaining market movements, surfacing budget insights, suggesting investment ideas, and answering questions in natural conversation.

Every interaction is rooted in the same promise: **help the user understand first, decide second, and act only when they're ready.**

### The Four Pillars

| Pillar | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| **01 — Learn** | Adaptive financial education that meets users at their level — from compound interest to ETFs — with AI-generated examples tied to their own goals. |
| **02 — Budget** | A simple, AI-powered budget tracker that doesn't just categorize spending — it explains patterns, flags risks, and connects habits to long-term goals. |
| **03 — Invest (Simulated)** | A paper trading environment where users build confidence before committing real money — with AI watching the market and surfacing explainable, user-controlled suggestions. |
| **04 — Ask** | An always-available AI companion chatbot that answers finance questions, discusses the user's portfolio or budget, and maintains conversational context across the app. |

