### 6.4 Stock Market Guidance

- Teach users how to **read stock charts** and understand common market indicators.
- Provide **real-time or near-real-time market data** with watchlists.
- Translate **financial news into simple language** — what happened, why it matters, and whether it affects the user's watchlist or learning goals.
- AI-driven explanations of market events and their implications.

**Market Monitoring Specificity:**
- **Initial markets:** US equities (NYSE, NASDAQ).
- **Trading hours logic:** Pre-market, regular session, after-hours — define which the AI monitors.
- **Notification system:**
  - Price alerts (user-configured thresholds)
  - Volatility alerts (automatic)
  - Portfolio change alerts (gains/losses beyond a threshold)

