## 28. Biggest Risks & Mitigation

| Risk | Why It Matters | Mitigation |
|------|---------------|------------|
| **Regulation** | Financial advice laws vary by jurisdiction | Education-first positioning; legal review before launch; clear disclaimers |
| **Trust** | Wrong recommendations erode confidence fast | Confidence scores, disclaimers, explainability, double confirmation |
| **Data costs** | Real-time stock data is expensive at scale | Start with free-tier APIs; upgrade as revenue allows |
| **AI hallucinations** | Fabricated financial data could cause real harm | Tight guardrails, RAG, human review layer, confidence thresholds |
| **Overfitting (ML)** | Model works in backtests, fails live | Rigorous backtesting, ensemble methods, ongoing retraining |
| **Black swan events** | AI breaks during crises when it's needed most | Prominent disclaimers, human oversight emphasis, circuit breakers |
| **Privacy/Compliance** | Financial data is sensitive; minors use the app | GDPR/CCPA compliance, encryption, parental consent, age restrictions |
| **AI model costs** | LLM API calls at scale are expensive | Token budgets, caching, fallback models, tiered usage |

